The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The LFS_TRACE macro is defined as empty (#define LFS_TRACE(__VA_ARGS__)), so the statement LFS_TRACE("lfs_file_rewind -> %d", err); expands to an empty/null statement (a no-op). That operation is executed but its removal would not affect program behaviour, i.e. it is dead code (the trace call is compiled out), which violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
